<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="would-modal-v">would <strong><em>modal v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /wʊd/    美 /wʊd/  </p>
<p>[will的过去式]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>将：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He said he would see me again the next day. 
他说第二天再来看我。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>打算；要：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He would not leave before he finished his work. 
完成工作之前他不会离开。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I promised that I would do my best. 
我答应过要尽力而为。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(从前) 常常：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>On Sundays he would come to see his aged parents.
他星期天常来看望年迈的父母。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Whenever Tom was angry, he would eat a lot. 
汤姆一生气就会吃很多东西。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>大概：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You would never know how much your mother cares about you. 
你大概永远不知道你妈妈有多关心你。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>如果能...的话：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If you would send me the papers, I should be grateful. 
如果你能把那些文件寄给我，我将万分感激。</p></div>

<h4 id="6">6.★ <strong>(如果...的话) 会：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You would have better grades if you studied hard every day. 
如果你每天都努力学习，就会有更好的成绩。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If I hadn't been faced with so many barriers,I wouldn't be where I am.
如果我没有面对过那么多的障碍，就不会有今天的我。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What would you do if they should disagree? 
万一他们反对，你会怎么办？</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Without his wartime experiences, Hemingway <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (不会写出) his famous novel A Farewell to Arms.  （2015 重庆改）  </li>
<li>I still remember my happy childhood when my mother <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ take me to Disneyland at weekends.   （2014 四川）<br />
A.might <br />
B.must <br />
C.would <br />
D.should  </li>
<li>They were abroad during the months when we were carrying out the investigation, or they <strong><em>_</em></strong>_(come) to our help.  （2014 浙江改）  </li>
<li>Days later, my brother called to say he was all right, but <strong><em>_</em></strong>_say where he was.  （2012 江苏）<br />
A.mustn’t<br />
B.shouldn’t <br />
C.wouldn’t <br />
D.mightn’t  </li>
<li>I’m sure you’d rather she went to school by bus, <strong><em>_</em></strong>_? <br />
A.hadn’t you <br />
B.wouldn’t you <br />
C.aren’t I <br />
D.didn’t she  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. wouldn’t have written  2. C  3. would have come  4. C  5. B  </p></div>